## Rust Standards

- Prefer `Result<T, E>` and `Option<T>` over panics in library code; use `?` operator to propagate
- Define errors with `thiserror`; expose `anyhow::Error` only at application boundaries
- Minimize `clone()` calls; prefer borrowing and lifetime annotations
- Use `#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]` on domain structs where sensible
- Keep `unsafe` blocks to an absolute minimum and document the invariants that make them safe
- Run `cargo fmt` and `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` before committing
- Write doc-tests for public API functions
